cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on learning motion of independently moving objects from stereo videos using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with understanding the motion of objects in a 3D space. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses deep learning techniques to learn the motion of objects. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely category as the paper involves developing a system that can learn and understand the motion of objects. Finally, computer graphics (cs.GR) is a possible category as the paper involves predicting 3D scene flow maps and instance masks, which are important in computer graphics applications.
